<paragraph id="IAS36_88" base="SL32310" principles="yes"><paranum>88</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 36"/><data name="paranum" value="88"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS36_P0317">When, as described in <xref id="IAS36_X0294" base="A36-238" href="IAS36_81.dita#IAS36_81">paragraph 81</xref>, goodwill relates to a <xref base="SL148451" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0096">cash&#x2011;generating unit<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0031"/></ph></xref> but has not been allocated to that unit, the unit shall be tested for impairment, whenever there is an indication that the unit may be impaired, by comparing the unit&#x2019;s <xref base="SL148450" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0095">carrying amount<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0026"/></ph></xref>, excluding any goodwill, with its <xref base="SL148458" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0106">recoverable amount<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0319"/></ph></xref>. Any <xref base="SL148457" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0105">impairment loss<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0176"/></ph></xref> shall be recognised in accordance with <xref id="IAS36_X0295" base="SL195794" href="IAS36_104.dita#IAS36_104">paragraph 104</xref>.</p></body></paragraph>